id, \u201cTell me about fasting the day of 'Ashura.\u201d Ibn Abbas said, \u201cWhen you see the crescent of the month of al-Muharram, count the days and wake up to fast on the ninth\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27560,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/15\/ibn-abbas-tasting-food-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":33627,"position":3},"title":"Ibn Abbas on Fasting: Permission to taste food while fasting if needed","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 15, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Qudamah reported: Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cThere is nothing wrong for a fasting person to taste food, vinegar, or something he wants to purchase.\u201d Ahmad ibn Hanbal said, \u201cI prefer to avoid tasting food, but there is no harm and nothing wrong if it\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33777,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/11\/16\/minimum-valid-marriage\/","url_meta":{"origin":33627,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Nikah: Minimum legal requirements for valid marriage","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 16, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThere is no marriage unless with a guardian and two credible witnesses. Any marriage contracted with less than that is invalid. If there is a dispute, the ruler is the guardian for one without a guardian.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34966,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/01\/17\/aishah-humility-deathbed\/","url_meta":{"origin":33627,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Death: Aisha\u2019s Godfearing humility on her deathbed","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 17, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abi Mulaykah reported: Ibn Abbas asked permission to see Aisha, may Allah be pleased with her, before her death while she was overcome with suffering. Aisha said, \u201cI am afraid he will praise me.\u201d It was said, \u201cHe is the cousin of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/33627","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=33627"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/33627\/revisions"}]